race.comment: Moderate maiden where MALAGARASI (6) will rightly go out well fancied. Made debut over 1300m at Northam and settled back before running on hard into fourth, beaten a couple of lengths. Looks likely to relish the extra ground and should be getting off the mark. LOVE OF FAR FA (3) is a long-time maiden but has done enough to appeal as the main danger. Has to overcome a terrible run though last time when back and wide and only jogged to the line. The start prior ran on well to place and if returning to that figure is right in this race. Just needs to bounce back. The race drops away very quickly beyond that. GRAVITY DEFYING (7) has fewer convictions than most, turning in a solid debut when grinding home into seventh. Better for it and the extra trip is a plus. BRITISH BONNIE (9) did run a better race last time, albeit beaten seven lengths over the mile. Longer trip suits and heading the right way. TALK OF THE YARD (8) is fitter for two runs in and gets a chance to show something.
